The paper proposes a framework for understanding agents with game behaviors through graph mining approaches. This involves utilizing the deviation between the real game outcome and the ideal game model to build networks for game processes. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for the use of machine learning techniques, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) for the focus on relationships between agents, Machine Learning (cs.LG) for the use of generative models, Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) for the study of social influences, and Game Theory (cs.GT) for the focus on game processes. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SOC, and cs.GT.
